      "ios/PTimer/Resources/LaunchPresetFilmCatalog.json"
    ],
    "version": "4.0.0",
    "description": "Validation cases for the bundled launch preset film catalog. The launch catalog ships only official manufacturer profiles in one of two shapes: formula (with optional sourceEvidence) or threshold + limited-guidance. PTIMER-160 retired the companion threshold rule from formula profiles — the formula owns its no-correction and source-range guards through the shared guarded `ReciprocityFormula` (Modified Schwarzschild: Tc = a × (Tm / Tref)^p + b). `sourceRangeThroughSeconds` is the source/fitting confidence boundary, not a calculation stop — inputs strictly above it still compute a numeric continuation, classified outside the source-backed range. PTIMER-162 will add a new formula family case alongside `modifiedSchwarzschild`. Unofficial practical profiles are bundled outside this catalog. No calculation table rules. User-facing reciprocity wording is constrained to No correction / Formula-derived / Beyond source range / No quantified prediction / Outside guidance; the legacy table-era vocabulary is forbidden."
  },
